The paper proposes a new global constraint that can be useful for various applications, including fuzzy constraint satisfaction and breaking symmetry. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The proposed algorithm for enforcing generalised arc consistency also indicates that the paper could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. Finally, the experimental results on several problem domains suggest that the paper could also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
